                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">mediocre</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer. Gabra
                        ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer is mentioned as the scribe in a few supplications (<locus target="#7ra">7ra</locus>, 12ra). Furthermore, he is referred to as the
                        husband of ʿĀmata Ṣǝyon (e.g., <locus target="#5va">5va</locus>, 11ra,
                        24ra). The same scribe produced Ms. GKM-012.<date>Late 19th century</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; groups of lines
                           on the incipit page of Texts I-1 and II; a few lines on the incipit page
                           of Texts I-2 and I-3; incipit of Text I-4 and of sections; the word
                           täfäśśǝḥi “rejoice”; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text
                           dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#5rb">5rb</locus>: short coloured (red, black) ornamental
                        band; interlaces.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- The readings in Text II are indicated in the upper
                              margin as follows: ጳውሎስ: <locus target="#29ra">fol. 29ra</locus> ዘሥራህ:
                                 <locus target="#31vb">fol. 31vb</locus> ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#34rb">fol. 34rb</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Omissions are inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 2vb, 12vb, 22ra. - Immediate corrections: words to be cancelled are indicated by thin red lines/dots above and below: fols. 4ra, 14va. - Erasures are sometimes marked with thin lines: e.g., fols. 32vb, 33ra. - Space for a miniature(?) is left unfilled on fols. 4v; the text is written only on the upper half of the leaf and continues on <locus target="#5ra">fol.  5ra</locus>. - Drawing of a cross in red: <locus target="#4v">fol.  4v</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
